'''Amir Hadžiahmetović''' ({{IPA|bs|âːmir xadʒiaxmêːtoʋitɕ|pron}}; born 8 March 1997) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|defensive midfielder]] for [[Premier League]] club [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]], on loan from [[Beşiktaş J.K.|Beşiktaş]]. Born in Denmark, he plays for the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

Hadžiahmetović started his professional career at [[FK Željezničar Sarajevo|Željezničar]], before joining [[Konyaspor]] in 2016. Seven years later, he moved to Beşiktaş, who loaned him to [[Çaykur Rizespor|Rizespor]] in 2024 and to Hull City in 2025.

A former youth international for Bosnia and Herzegovina, Hadžiahmetović made his senior international debut in 2020, earning over 30 [[Cap (sport)|caps]] since.

==Club career==

===Željezničar===
Hadžiahmetović started playing football at his hometown club [[Nexø Boldklub Bornholm|Nexø Boldklub]], before joining the youth academy of [[FK Željezničar Sarajevo|Željezničar]] in 2009. In July 2014, he signed his first professional contract with the team.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/128622/za-zeljeznicar-potpisao-doskorasnji-kadet-amir-hadziahmetovic|title=Za Željezničar potpisao doskorašnji kadet Amir Hadžiahmetović|website=avaz.ba|date=31 July 2014|access-date=1 August 2014|language=bs}}</ref> He made his professional debut against [[FK Olimpik|Olimpic]] on 2 August at the age of 17.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/zeljina-mladost-ima-snage-plavi-slavili-na-otoci/137105|title=Željina mladost ima snage, Plavi slavili na Otoci|website=sportsport.ba|date=2 August 2014|access-date=2 August 2014|language=bs}}</ref> On 13 May 2015, he scored his first professional goal in a triumph over [[FK Mladost Velika Obarska|Mladost Velika Obarska]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/premijer-liga-trijumfi-sarajeva-i-zeljeznicara-zvijezda-se-vratila-iz-mrtvih/150513131|title=Premijer liga: Trijumfi Sarajeva i Željezničara, Zvijezda se vratila iz mrtvih|website=klix.ba|date=13 May 2015|access-date=15 May 2015|language=bs}}</ref>

===Konyaspor===
In February 2016, Hadžiahmetović was transferred to Turkish outfit [[Konyaspor]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/milion-na-grbavici-zeljo-dobija-rekordno-obestecenje-za-amira-hadziahmetovica/214892|title=Milion na Grbavici: Željo dobija rekordno obeštećenje za Amira Hadžiahmetovića|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=1 February 2016|access-date=1 February 2016|language=be}}</ref> He made his official debut for the side in a [[2015–16 Turkish Cup#Quarter-finals|Turkish Cup]] game against [[Beşiktaş J.K.|Beşiktaş]] on 10 February.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/40391-kup-turske-bajic-sjajno-pogodio-iz-slobodnjaka-hadziahmetovic-debitovao-za-konyu|title=Kup Turske: Bajić sjajno pogodio iz slobodnjaka, Hadžiahmetović debitovao za Konyu|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=10 February 2016|access-date=10 February 2016|language=bs}}</ref> Seven weeks later, he made his league debut against [[Gençlerbirliği S.K.|Gençlerbirliği]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oslobodjenje.ba/sport/fudbal/ino-fudbal/bajic-igrao-70-minuta-hadziahmetovic-debitovao-u-novoj-pobjedi-konyaspora-38618|title=Bajić igrao 70 minuta, Hadžiahmetović debitovao u novoj pobjedi Konyaspora|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=2 April 2016|access-date=2 April 2016|language=bs}}</ref> On 19 November, he scored his first goal for the team in a defeat of [[Gaziantepspor]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/zeljina-djeca-vodila-konyaspor-do-velike-pobjede/214491|title=Željina djeca vodila Konyaspor do velike pobjede|website=sportsport.ba|date=19 November 2016|access-date=20 November 2016|language=bs}}</ref> He won his first title with Konyaspor, club's first trophy ever, on 31 May 2017, by beating [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]] in the [[2016–17 Turkish Cup|Turkish Cup]] final.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/bajic-hadziahmetovic-i-milosevic-sa-konyasporom-u-finalu-savladali-basaksehir-i-osvojili-kup-turske/170531147|title=Bajić, Hadžiahmetović i Milošević sa Konyasporom u finalu savladali Başakşehir i osvojili Kup Turske|website=klix.ba|date=31 May 2017|access-date=1 June 2017|language=bs}}</ref>

Hadžiahmetović played his 100th match for the squad against [[Sivasspor]] on 21 June 2020.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/302770-hadziahmetovic-odigrao-jubilarni-100-mec-za-konyu-i-asistirao-milosevicu-za-gol|title=Hadžiahmetović odigrao jubilarni 100. meč za Konyu i asistirao Miloševiću za gol|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=21 June 2020|access-date=22 June 2020|language=bs}}</ref>

In July 2021, he extended his contract with Konyaspor until June 2024.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/amir-hadziahmetovic-produzio-saradnju-sa-konyasporom/94977|title=Amir Hadžiahmetović produžio saradnju sa Konyasporom|website=faktor.ba|date=9 July 2021|access-date=10 July 2021|language=bs}}</ref>

===Beşiktaş===
In February 2023, Hadžiahmetović moved to Beşiktaş on a deal until June 2027.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/amir-hadziahmetovic-potpisao-za-besiktas-u-zeljeznicaru-zadovoljno-trljaju-ruke/230131072|title=Amir Hadžiahmetović potpisao za Beşiktaş, u Željezničaru zadovoljno trljaju ruke|website=klix.ba|date=2 February 2023|access-date=2 February 2023|language=bs}}</ref> He made his competitive debut for the team on 4 February against Sivasspor.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/hadziahmetovic-debitovao-u-porazu-besiktasa/147465|title=Hadžiahmetović debitovao u porazu Beşiktaşa|website=faktor.ba|date=4 February 2023|access-date=4 February 2023|language=bs}}</ref> On 30 April, he scored his first goal for Beşiktaş in a victory over [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/826154/hadziahmetovic-pogodio-u-istanbulskom-derbiju-i-srusio-lidera-turske|title=Hadžiahmetović pogodio u istanbulskom derbiju i srušio lidera Turske|website=avaz.ba|date=30 April 2023|access-date=1 May 2023|language=bs}}</ref>

In January 2024, Hadžiahmetović suffered a severe knee injury, which was diagnosed as an [[Anterior cruciate ligament injury|anterior cruciate ligament tear]] and was ruled out for at least six months. Over seven months after the injury, on 12 August, he returned to the pitch.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://scsport.ba/amir-hadziahmetovic-se-vratio-na-teren-nakon-osam-mjeseci-teska-povreda-je-iza-bh-reprezentativca|title=Amir Hadžiahmetović se vratio na teren nakon osam mjeseci: Teška povreda je iza bh. reprezentativca|website=scsport.ba|date=13 August 2024|access-date=15 August 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

He won his first piece of silverware with the club on 23 May, when they beat [[Trabzonspor]] in the [[2023–24 Turkish Cup|Turkish Cup]] final.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fokus.ba/sport/fudbal/besiktas-osvojio-kup-turske-visca-igrao-cijeli-mec-hadziahmetovic-zbog-ozljede-propustio-finale/3184941|title=Beşiktaş osvojio Kup Turske, Višća igrao cijeli meč, Hadžiahmetović zbog ozljede propustio finale|website=fokus.ba|date=23 May 2024|access-date=25 May 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

In August, he was sent on a season-long loan to [[Çaykur Rizespor|Rizespor]], but was recalled in February 2025.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oslobodjenje.ba/sport/fudbal/ino-fudbal/ole-gunnar-solskjaer-obavio-vazan-poziv-amir-hadziahmetovic-ima-novi-klub-1019825|title=Ole Gunnar Solskjær obavio važan poziv, Amir Hadžiahmetović ima novi klub|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=10 February 2025|access-date=10 February 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

In September 2025, he was loaned to English side [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]] until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/amir-hadziahmetovic-stigao-u-englesku-novi-pocetak-pod-vodstvom-sergeja-jakirovica|title=Amir Hadžiahmetović stigao u Englesku: Novi početak pod vodstvom Sergeja Jakirovića|website=n1info.ba|date=1 September 2025|access-date=1 September 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

==International career==
Hadžiahmetović represented [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] at all youth levels.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oslobodjenje.ba/sport/fudbal/ino-fudbal/amir-hadziahmetovic-nadam-se-da-cu-za-seniorsku-reprezentaciju-zaigrati-u-2020-godini-174849|title=Amir Hadžiahmetović: Nadam se da ću za seniorsku reprezentaciju zaigrati u 2020. godini|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=5 December 2019|access-date=5 December 2019|language=bs}}</ref>

In August 2020, he received his first senior call up, for [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League A#Group 1|2020–21 UEFA Nations League A]] games against [[Italy national football team|Italy]] and [[Poland national football team|Poland]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/307199-dusan-bajevic-pozvao-menala-kovacevica-i-hadziahmetovica-za-meceve-sa-italijom-i-poljskom|title=Dušan Bajević pozvao Menala, Kovačevića i Hadžiahmetovića za mečeve sa Italijom i Poljskom|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=26 August 2020|access-date=28 August 2020|language=bs}}</ref> He debuted against the former on 4 September.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/desetkovani-zmajevi-osvojili-bod-u-gostima-kod-cetverostrukih-prvaka-svijeta/64181|title=Desetkovani Zmajevi osvojili bod u gostima kod četverostrukih prvaka svijeta|website=faktor.ba|date=4 September 2020|access-date=6 September 2020|language=bs}}</ref>

In June 2026, Hadžiahmetović was named in Bosnia and Herzegovina's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/barbarez-poslao-konacan-spisak-fifa-i-jedno-ime-otputovalo-u-ameriku-ali-nije-na-listi|title=Barbarez poslao konačan spisak FIFA-i: Jedno ime otputovalo u Ameriku, ali nije na listi|website=sportske.ba|date=3 June 2026|access-date=3 June 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

